    • Constructor Detail

      • LabeledSymmetricMatrix

        public LabeledSymmetricMatrix(double[][] values)
        Creates a new SymmetricMatrix with the given double values. The first index of the double array represents the row index and the second index represents the column index.

        The following array: 

         {{1.0, 2.0, 3.0}, {2.0, 5.0, 6.0}, {3.0, 6.0, 9.0}}
        result in the matrix: 
         1.0  2.0  3.0
 2.0  5.0  6.0
 3.0  6.0  9.0
        Parameters:
        values - The values of the matrix.

      • getStringRepresentation

        public java.lang.String getStringRepresentation()
        Description copied from interface: LabeledMatrix
        Returns a string representation of the labelled matrix such that a CSV compatible format is achieved. Numbers are rounded to 6 decimal places to keep visual layout.

        The following symmetric matrix with the labels L1, L2, L3 result in the following string representation: 

         ,L1,L2,L3
 L1,1.000000,2.000000,3.000000
 L2,2.000000,4.000000,5.000000
 L3,3.000000,5.000000,8.000000
        Specified by:
        getStringRepresentation in interface LabeledMatrix<LabelType>
        Returns:
        a CSV-like string representation
